{"id":"45f61c46-8b14-498b-8269-b8ded90ba586","userId":"e8f217b2-1fcc-414b-848e-ba2547929ee4","role":"assistant","content":"I'm so sorry to hear that you're struggling with feelings of depression and moving on from your ex-girlfriend. It's completely normal to feel this way, and it takes time to heal and process your emotions. Can you tell me more about what's been on your mind and heart since the breakup? What are some of the thoughts, memories, or feelings that you're finding it hard to let go of?\n\nIt might be helpful to acknowledge that it's okay to grieve the loss of the relationship and to give yourself permission to feel your emotions. Sometimes, allowing ourselves to feel the pain and sadness can actually help us move forward. Have you tried any self-care activities or coping mechanisms that have helped you feel a little better, even if it's just for a short time? \n\nIf you're finding it difficult to manage your emotions or if you're experiencing intense feelings of sadness, I want to remind you that it's always okay to reach out for support. Consider talking to a trusted friend, family member, or mental health professional who can provide you with guidance and care. They can help you develop a plan to work through your feelings and move forward in a healthy way.","createdAt":"2026-05-15T15:36:15.359Z","_id":"CyPUIEPiBWMptX7T"}
